orp. this month will ship a new version of its MacVisionvideo digitizer that improves resolution and image stability, companyofficials said.andM;MacVision is designed to capture two- and three-dimensional images andconvert them into Macintosh graphics files.andP;  The new model increases thevideo bandwidth and improves horizontal resolution by as much as 20 percent,officials of the San Jose, Calif., company said.andM;The new version is priced at $499.95; current users can upgrade for $200.andM;Koala Technologies can be reached at (408) 287-6311.andO;</TEXT></DOC>